my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Back-up ECDIS unit always ready & available for immediate use;
b) ECDIS system used type approved hardware;
c) All equipment in protected area;
d) Installation and Maintenance done in accordance with makers instructions;
e) Spare dongle on board - back in case of damage;

a)Type approved ECDIS software used;
b) No other software used on system; 
c) Back-up ECDIS unit always ready & available for immediate use; 
d) ECDIS not connected to any other outside computer;
e) ECDIS not connected to ship's WiFi network;
f) 24/7 technical service support from Transas ( makers) : +46 771 460 100 / Email : service@transas.com
g) Back up for the software on CD- always on board;

a) Back up power to ECDIS by the UPS system -always in operation;
b) All radio equipment has secondary power source as per GMDSS regulations;
c) Emergency Generator start-up & online within 30 seconds automatically;
d) Batteries (including UPS) maintained regularly.

a) Alarms always in use to warn of failures;
b) ECDIS stations are connected separately to GPS via NMEA Splitter;
c) Alarm set to check errors between two GPS units;
d) The primary positioning fixing system (GPS) regularly cross-checked. Manual fixing position function MUST BE used regularly. Any cross-checking between GPS position fixing and manual position fixing via other methods is logged.
e) Radar overlay or ARPA fixed targets used to confirm vessel position.
f) Procedure to increase bridge manning and dedicate resource solely to safe navigation IN CASE OF FAILURE.

a) Only Transas software are installed on ECDIS computers;
b) Units are not connected in any way to another system;
c) Only Transas updates allowed to be used;
d) Anti-virus installed on main communication computer which is used for ECDIS updates;
e) Use only the Dedicated USB stick for data transfer - CLEARLY MARKED.

a) Procedure to update route charts during passage planning and consequently during passage on weekly basis;
b) Updates obtain via e-mail (in real time - automatic reply from Transas);
c)  Indication is given by the ECDIS to which week charts are updated;
d) Updates to ENC's are sequential, ECDIS will indicate if an update is missing;
e) CD with weekly updates are received from the office in suitable ports;
f) Base CD's are received quarterly in suitable ports;

a) Only Masters and Deck Officers with the appropriate generic and type specific (Transas 4000) can be OOW on a ECDIS Certified Vessel;
b) Prior to taking charge of Navigational Watch Master and Deck Officer are familiarized with the ECDIS equipment and ECDIS Familiarization form is to be completed in full.
c) ECDIS Videotel Course available on board (Course 2000) is to be undertaken.
